# Plan Execution Loop

> **Thesis:** One plan slice at a time — implement, evidence-based audit (≥90/100, file:line proof required), fix, re-audit — then next slice. Parent agent orchestrates; subagents implement and audit.
>
> **Invoke when:** User says "run the plan", "execute slice X", or points at `docs/plans/*.md` for implementation.

## Per-slice loop (do not skip)

```
1. IMPLEMENT — Task subagent: read plan slice only; implement; run verification commands; update Progress row
2. AUDIT   — Task subagent (readonly): grade /100 vs slice acceptance with file:line evidence; PASS only if ≥90 and every criterion has proof
3. FIX     — if FAIL: Task subagent applies audit fix list; no scope creep
4. RE-AUDIT — repeat 2–3 until ≥90 with full evidence
5. NEXT SLICE — only after current slice PASS
```

## Subagent prompts must include

- Exact slice ID and file path to plan section
- Acceptance criteria from plan (copy verbatim)
- Verification commands (`npm run test:coverage`, `check_spec_drift.sh`, etc.)
- Forbidden scope (other slices, unrelated refactors)
- Evidence rule: every deduction needs `path:line` citation; every PASS criterion needs `path:line` proof or automatic FAIL
- **Fresh grade (audit dispatches only):** grade the artifact **as it exists now** — start at 100, deduct only for **current** gaps with `path:line` proof. Do not reward "improvement since last pass", prior fix lists, or Progress table history. Parent must not anchor with prior scores (see Re-audit below).
- "Return: grade, PASS/FAIL, evidence table, fix list, files changed, blockers"

## Evidence-based audit (mandatory)

Audit subagents grade **evidence**, not vibes. A numeric score without citations is invalid.

**For every deduction** — cite `path:line` (or `path:line-line` for a range) showing the gap. Example: `-5 Scope: backend/internal/handler/foo.go:42 — touches bar.go, outside slice file list`.

**For every slice acceptance criterion** — cite `path:line` (or command output) proving it is met. If the auditor cannot find proof after reading the diff and running verification commands, that criterion is **automatic FAIL** regardless of the running score.

**Score math:**

- Start at 100.
- Deduct per finding with cited evidence only — no uncited deductions.
- Uncited "looks good" claims do not count toward PASS.
- Final grade = 100 minus cited deductions. If any acceptance criterion lacks proof → **FAIL** even when grade ≥90.

**Required audit return format:**

```
Grade: NN/100 — PASS | FAIL
Acceptance evidence:
  - [criterion verbatim]: path:line — one-line proof
Deductions:
  - [-N Dimension]: path:line — finding
Fix list: (ordered, only if FAIL)
Blockers: (only if FAIL)
```

Parent agent: reject audit output missing the evidence table or with blank acceptance proofs — re-dispatch audit with "evidence required" before FIX or NEXT SLICE.

### Re-audit — avoid accumulation bias

Fix loops invite **score drift** when auditors see prior grades and nudge scores up. Re-audits grade the **current artifact only**, not deltas from the last grade.

**Audit subagent (re-audit):** Same rubric as pass 1. No prior scores or fix-list history in context. Fixed issues = no deduction, not bonus points. No `path:line` proof → criterion fails.

**Parent agent (re-audit dispatch):** Do not paste prior grades into the prompt. Reject audits that cite "pass N fixed X" without re-verifying X in the current file.

## Parent agent responsibilities

- Read plan slice before dispatching — do not dump whole plan into subagent
- Reject audit subagent output without file:line evidence — re-dispatch, do not accept inflated scores
- On re-audit dispatch: omit prior pass scores from the prompt; reject grade inflation without cited gap closure (see Re-audit — accumulation bias)
- Run `scripts/check_spec_drift.sh origin/main` before commit when handler/service touched
- Commit per slice or logical batch after PASS; never commit with audit below 90 or missing evidence
- Update `docs/plans/*.md` Progress table after each PASS

## Audit dimensions (default weights)

| Dimension | What to check | Evidence required |
|-----------|---------------|-------------------|
| Completeness | All deliverables in slice scope | `path:line` per deliverable, or FAIL |
| Accuracy | Paths, commands, plan citations match repo | `path:line` or command output |
| Acceptance | Slice-specific gates met | `path:line` or test output per criterion |
| Scope | No slice creep; spec sync if required | `path:line` for out-of-scope edits, or `rg`/diff showing clean scope |
| Verification | Commands run, exit 0 | Paste exit code + relevant output snippet |

## Contract closeout (from `slice-and-ship`)

Before commit on backend slices: spec sync or `[skip-spec(module): reason]`; run `check_spec_drift.sh`.

## Parallel slices within one plan

Independent slices (e.g. B4a ∥ B4b ∥ B4c) may run as parallel **implement** subagents in the **same working tree** when they touch disjoint files. Each slice still gets its own **audit → fix → re-audit** loop before merge.

Pre-flight: `rg` plan slice file lists — if two slices touch the same file, run them sequentially.

## Multiple plans in parallel (worktrees required)

When running **two or more plans** concurrently (each with its own execution loop), **do not share one working tree.** Each plan gets isolated git state — same rules as `parallel-subagents` "When subagents will commit code".

```
Parent branch (e.g. steve-dev)
├── worktree: ../golid-plan-a  →  branch plan/a-short-name  →  docs/plans/foo.md loop
└── worktree: ../golid-plan-b  →  branch plan/b-short-name  →  docs/plans/bar.md loop
```

**Setup (parent agent):**

```bash
git worktree add -b plan/<name> ../golid-<name> HEAD
# Dispatch plan execution loop subagent with working_directory = that worktree path
```

**Land back on parent branch:**

1. Pre-flight: `rg` both plans for overlapping file paths — resolve or serialize conflicting plans
2. Cherry-pick **one commit at a time** from each plan branch (smaller/additive plan first) — see `parallel-subagents` cherry-pick loop
3. After each pick: build + test; fix conflicts before next pick
4. Run full verification on parent: `check_spec_drift.sh`, `npm run typecheck`, `go test ./...`
5. `git worktree remove` + `git branch -D plan/<name>` when landed

**Forbidden on parent repo while worktrees run:** `git reset --hard`, `git clean -fd`, `git checkout --force` — can destroy uncommitted work in sibling worktrees.

## Anti-patterns

| Bad | Good |
|-----|------|
| Implement B4a–c in one pass | B4a PASS → then B4b |
| Two plans editing same branch simultaneously | One worktree per plan |
| Bulk cherry-pick plan commits | One commit at a time |
| Audit whole plan at end | Audit each slice before next |
| Skip audit because "tests pass" | Audit grades behavior + docs + scope |
| Commit at 82/100 | Fix loop until ≥90 |
| Grade 92 with no file:line citations | Reject output; re-audit with evidence |
| "Criterion met" without path:line proof | Automatic FAIL for that criterion |
| Vague deductions ("could be cleaner") | Cited finding or no deduction |
| Re-audit prompt includes prior scores or sympathy grading | Fresh grade from 100; re-verify fixes at `path:line` only |

